  <entry>
    <title type="html"><![CDATA[How to Check for User Access or Permission in Drupal 8]]></title>
    <link href="http://drupal8notes.github.io/how-to-check-for-user-access-in-drupal-8/"/>
    <updated>2014-10-30T00:50:17-05:00</updated>
    <id>http://drupal8notes.github.io/how-to-check-for-user-access-in-drupal-8</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>In Drupal 7, you would use the user_access function to check for user access. Here&rsquo;s how to do it in Drupal 8.</p>

<figure class='code'><figcaption><span>How to check for permission in Drupal 8</span></figcaption><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
<span class='line-number'>5</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='php'><span class='line'><span class="c1">// Get the current user</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="nv">$user</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nx">\Drupal</span><span class="o">::</span><span class="na">currentUser</span><span class="p">();</span>
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'><span class="c1">// Check for permission</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="nv">$user</span><span class="o">-&gt;</span><span class="na">hasPermission</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;access administration menu&#39;</span><span class="p">);</span>
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>

]]></content>
